             were indicted, for that <rs id="t17910608-41-off243" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17910608-41-off243" type="offenceCategory" value="royalOffences"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17910608-41-off243" type="offenceSubcategory" value="taxOffences"></interp>
               they, on the <rs id="t17910608-41-cd244" type="crimeDate">31st of January, 1788</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17910608-41-off243 t17910608-41-cd244"></join>, in the county of <placeName id="t17910608-41-crimeloc245">Devon</placeName>
                     <interp inst="t17910608-41-crimeloc245" type="placeName" value="Devon"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17910608-41-crimeloc245" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                     <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17910608-41-off243 t17910608-41-crimeloc245"></join>, on 
                     <persName id="t17910608-41-person451">
                        John
                         Felton
                     <interp inst="t17910608-41-person451" type="surname" value="Felton"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17910608-41-person451" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17910608-41-person451" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  , then acting in aid and assistance of 
                     <persName id="t17910608-41-person452">
                        Thomas
                         Bradley
                     <interp inst="t17910608-41-person452" type="surname" value="Bradley"></interp>
